<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7192937>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Bauhinia arleneae—A: flowering branch; B: detail of the branch at the petiole attachment showing extrafloral nectaries; C–E: upper (C) and lower (D) leaf surface and a detail of the lower surface (E); F: flower in frontal view; G: detail of the petal; H: stipitate gynoecium; I: detail of the staminal column minutely whitish tomentose on the inner surface; J: stamen; K: anther; L: immature fruit and M: seeds. Drawing by R. Carvalho based on the holotype." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7192937/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7192939>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Bauhinia arleneae–A: General aspects of the branch showing leaf disposition; B: Immature fruit; C: floral buds and D: flower. Holotype field photos: A.C.B. Santos" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7192939/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7192943>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Map of Northeastern Brazil showing the state of Bahia (BA) and the distribution of Bauhinia arleneae (red circles)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7192943/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

